              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div>The patient was admitted to the hospital with progressive subungual melanosis in the hallux of the right foot lasting more than 4 years. No pseudo-Hutchinson signs were noted during the initial evaluation. After resection, the tumor was pathologically diagnosed as subungual melanocytic nevus, and the defect of the nail matrix was repaired with a lateral toe pulp island flap based on the plantar digital artery. A thorough clinical evaluation and follow-up tests were carried out to monitor the patient's recovery after surgery.</div>"
